title: For Sale:  (30-06) with Cody Letter Great rifle in a rare caliber
postcontent: This great old rifle was built on May 4th 1911 by Winchester. There is some pitting in the nickel steel receiver, this is common in old 95's. The rust blued barrel retains most of the bluing, no rust, and has a great bore. This old repeater has the famous Climbing Lyman rear sight, probably from the factory. The rear dovetail has a filler plug that looks like it's a sways been there. Teddy Roosevelt's favorite rifle was a 1895.Winchester he named Big Medicne. The 19-03 was the U.S. Military 'official caliber for a very short time. A guy named Spitizer designed a pointed full metal jacket bullet in 1906 to replace the big, round bullet designed for the 03 Springfield ergo the 30-06 we all know and love. Most of the 30-03's went to the Mexicans fighting their Revolution. ( we had a bunch of surplus ammo).this rifle fires 30-06 ammo through it's shiny bore like a champ. I have had this fine piece of history a long time. The stock has some dents, it appears that it rode in a rifle rack a good bit. The wood has no cracks, it's a rock solid rifle. I can send a lot of photos. It even has some black ebony or buffalo horn in it's forearm. It is all original. I saw one like this in rough shape for sale with a price of $3000.00.
